We have recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to enjoin the HRMO the following:

To stipulate in the contract of service, specific highly technical duties and responsibilities that requires skills/ expertise and compare those against their actual outputs/ accomplishments to ascertain whether or not they are able to deliver their functions expected, otherwise the hiring is unjustified;

Stop the practice of hiring consultants for tasks which do not require expertise and that can be performed by the regular employees to avoid incurrence of additional expenditure disadvantageous to the agency; 

Identify those consultants whose scope of work overlap with the functions of the other consultants because it is an indication that there is a need to reduce their number in order to avoid wastage of public funds; and

Require the consultants to submit curriculum vitae and other relevant information that would support their credentials and eligibilities in their chosen field of expertise and for the management to create a databank of the consultants’ credentials/qualifications in order to determine whether their accomplishments are conformable to their qualifications and to justify their appointment as consultants.

The Property and Accounting Office maintain complete an accurate PPELC for each category of PPE pursuant to Section 114 on the NGAS Manual for LGUs in order to promote effective monitoring and controls over PPE;
A reconciliation of the Property and Accounting records be done after the conduct of physical count;
The Inventory Committee submit the Physical Inventory Reports to the Property Officer and COA Office for verification and reconciliation of the result of the physical inventory with the complete Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards and the Property Cards maintained by the Property and Accounting Office;
Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE)/ Property Acknowledgement Receipt (PAR) be maintained and renewed renewal of the said document every three years in accordance with the Instructions on the use of ARE/PAR; and
The Property and Accounting Office comply with the prescribed procedures in COA Circular No. 89-296 on the disposal of unserviceable PPE, if any

To ensure that financial assistance granted is valid, regular and reasonable, we recommended and the Management agreed to:
Formulate policies and guidelines or adopt the policies and guidelines promulgated by DSWD on the grant of financial assistance under the AICS program to strengthen the controls employed in the selection of eligible beneficiaries;
Ensure that the MSWDO strictly assess and evaluate all applicants requesting financial assistance out of the AICS program including the identification of nearest kin who serves as the claimant;
Refrain from granting grocery as burial assistance to non-eligible beneficiaries and require written explanation from the concerned municipal official/ employee for the noted observations for the procurement and distribution of groceries to the beneficiaries; and
Require the Municipal Accountant to be more circumspect in reviewing completeness of supporting documents.

In view of the foregoing, we have recommended that:

Management create an Inventory Committee that will conduct a complete annual physical count of PPE in accordance with Section 124 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Vol. I. A representative of the Auditor be invited to witness the inventory taking for this purpose;

The Property and Accounting Office maintain complete an accurate PPELC for each category of PPE pursuant to Section 114 on the NGAS Manual for LGUs in order to promote effective monitoring and controls over PPE;

A reconciliation of the Property and Accounting records be done after the conduct of physical count;

The Inventory Committee submit the Physical Inventory Reports to the Property Officer and COA Office for verification and reconciliation of the result of the physical inventory with the complete Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards and the Property Cards maintained by the Property and Accounting Office;

Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE)/ Property Acknowledgement Receipt (PAR) be maintained and renewed renewal of the said document every three years in accordance with the Instructions on the use of ARE/PAR; and

The Property and Accounting Office comply with the prescribed procedures in COA Circular No. 89-296 on the disposal of unserviceable PPE, if any

We have recommended that the Management:

provide justification on the hiring of 312 job order and casuals ; 

ensure that hiring of JOs and casual personnel is on account of necessity and urgency of the agency ;

limit the hiring of job order and casual personnel to complement only the office where transactions are voluminous;

ensure that the functions and responsibilities of the contracted employees be well-defined and clear in the contracts to facilitate proper evaluation of work performed by the employees ; and

formulate hiring plan of job orders and casuals to strengthen internal controls pertaining thereto.

